CONTROLS
~~~~~~~~
The game requires a Mouse and the erm, Keyboard. The mouse is used to scroll
the screen by moving the pointer to the edge of the screen you wish to
scroll. The Icons at the bottom of the screen are used by clicking on them
using the Mouse. Some weapons may bring up another panel after they've been
clicked on, this will give greater control over the weapons.

Using the additional Keyboard controls it is possible to play this game 
completely without a mouse!

Additional keyboard controls are as follows:

Key:                 Effect:
~~~                  ~~~~~~
HELP                 Automatically scrolls the screen to find the current
                     player. Very useful and quick.

F1-F8                Select Icons on panels (Hot keys for the Mouse)
SPACE                Hot Key for activating the current weapon
CURSOR KEYS          Moves the active character (Up cursor Jumps).
                     The cursor keys will also aim the Bazooka weapon once
                     it has been activated. 
SHIFT KEY (Either)   Jumps (Used instead of the up arrow - for those who
                     prefer it.
CTRL                 Also Jumps. Added because my shift keys are dying.
Numeric Keys         Bad luck A600 owners! Still, it's only required
           as a mouse-like replacement. It scrolls the screen ie.
           4 = Left Scroll, 6 = Right Scroll, 8 = Up Scroll
           and 2 = Down Scroll. Finally 5 = Home in on Beastie (Same
           as the <Help> Key)
< and >              In the "Bazooka" panel mode, these will control the 
           power-meter. This can be used instead of the mouse. 
ESC                  Quit back to main menu
1                    Display Player 1's energy percentage left
2                    Display Player 2's energy percentage left
Left AMIGA key & N   This will Multitask back to DOS. Useful for Hard Disk
                     users. Could also act like a Pause button. An official
                     "Pause" option has not been added due to the fact that
                     this game is two player only, so therefore, pausing
                     is simply not required. NOTE: This feature has been 
           disabled in this demo version.

The Joystick can also be used to move the character instead of the Cursor
keys, but the Cursor keys are more accurate, so I'd reccommend those.

Also the CD³² CONTROL PADS are Supported! The whole game can be
controlled via CD³² control pad - no need to touch the keyboard!

A CD³² Control pad plugged into the Joystick port:

Cursor Control Pad        =  Direction of Beasties Movement (Left, Right, Jump)

Big << and >> buttons     =  Scroll the Screen Left and Right

Green and Yellow buttons  =  Cycle through your weaponary

Red Button       =  Fire

Blue Button               =  Home in on current Beastie.

In Bazooka Mode:
~~ ~~~~~~~ ~~~~
Big << and >> Buttons     =  Power Select

Cursor Pad                =  Left & Right to control angles of fire

Red Button                =  Fire

A note about falling: When your character falls from a high point, you have
no control over the Beastie until you hit the ground. However, if you jump
of a high point, you can use Left and Right to drift the Beastie. After the
Beastie has either fallen or jumped & driften down approximately 70 pixels,
the beastie will be rendered unconcious causing an energy loss of 10%.

If you have either fallen or gotten blown into the sky, once your Beastie
has smacked back onto ground, he will indent the ground. This means, if the
Beastie lands on a thin bit of ground, he will go straight through it.

GAMEPLAY
~~~~~~~~
The charactor will move over flat ground and bumpy ground, but when the
gradient (steepness) is too steep, your character will not be able to move
over it, he/she may have to Jump over/onto it, but even this will have no
effect if the ground is too steep. Best way is to simply dig through it,
or better still, blow it away!

The Icons at the bottom of the screen show the current weapon selected (With
White box surrounding it) and beneath each icon is the amount of that weapon
you have left. When it reaches Zero, it is obviously inactive.

Each time a player takes a shot or uses an icon, the screen will
automatically select the next player. Make things simple, each player gets
one go. He/She can move as far as possible around the screen, but as soon as
a weapon is used, that's the player's go over with.

Your energy will be displayed above your head for a few seconds each time
you are hit. You begin with 100% Health although this can be changed via
the menu option (See Menu Options: Not in this demo version!)

You will notice that at the very top of the screen, there's a text-bar.
This will have general comments in as you progess through the game. It is
also there as a Help type accessory. For example, clicking on an icon on the
panel at the bottom of the screen, will not only select that weapon, but
the Text-bar will inform you what that weapon is (Incase the icons are a little
unclear!). 

When you get shot or caught up in an explosion, your Beastie will be sent 
flying. When he lands, as long as he's still got some energy left, he will
re-generate his body, leaving his old dead body on the grounds. 

The energy goes down like this:
----------------------------------------------------
Bazooka Hit:           Varies (Next Paragraph)
Shot Gun Hit:                15% deduction
Dynamite Hit:                50% deduction
Fall more then 70 pixels:    05% deduction
Being blown off the screen:  Sudden Death!
----------------------------------------------------

The Bazooka can be a lethal or lethal-less weapon. You will notice after
you have selected it, that there is an energy bar which you drag your
mouse arrow across - the more full it is with red, the more powerful
the shot. The more powerful the shot - the more energy it will reduce your
opponent by and the faster the missile goes.

Just above and below the bar are three marks: First mark at the start of
the bar, second mark half way across and third mark at the end.

If the energy bar is less then the first red marker, this means, if the missile
hits your opponent, it will just take -5 hit points of him/her. If it's between 
the first and middle marker, it will reduce their energy by -20. Between the 
middle and end marker, it takes -30 and anything past the final marker takes
-40. Here's a table for easy viewing:

------------------------------------------------------------
Less then first red marker:      -5  energy deduction
Between the first and middle markers:   -20 energy deduction
Between the middle and end markers:     -30 energy deduction
Past end marker:        -40 energy deduction
------------------------------------------------------------

Pressing 1 or 2 depending on which player you are; will display your current
health.

You have infinite Shot Gun bullets, but the rest of weapons are limited.

The game ends when a player has lost all of his/her health.

Official (Laws of me!) ways of dying include:
Being gunned to death (Lack of energy),
Being shot off the side of the screen,
Falling through the bottomless ground.

Here's a list of the icons and what they do (From left to right):

1: Fire!                      Activates the currently selected icon.
2: Shot Gun:                  Shoots a horizontal shot. Infinite ammunition.
                              Upon hitting your opposition, he/she will go
                              flying (Further then from the explosion
                              of dynamite or Bazooka) giving the advantage
                              of maybe blowing the opposition of the screen
                              (Sudden death!)
3: Bazooka:                   Missile can be positioned using the cursor
                              keys once activated. ie. After selected, click
                              on the "Fire!" icon for another panel to
                              appear. The Beastie can't be moved, but can
                              point his gun in seven increments (ie. Right,
                              Left, Up, Up-Right, Up-Left, Down-Right and
                              Down-Left). Clicking on the second "Fire" will
                              shoot the missile. Remember: what goes up,
                              must come down!

                              If you find the Beastie is not positioned
                              correctly, you can click on the "Back" icon
                              and it'll take you back to the main panel
                              where you can reposition your Beastie.

                              Don't forget, there is a Power-Meter for the
                              Bazooka, if you don't set it from Zero, the
                              missile 'll blow up in your face! Nice!
4: TNT:                       Most powerful weapon. Stick a stick near
                              someone and run! They can be dropped down
                              holes etc, once lit, you have a few seconds to
                              run before the explosion takes place.
5: Dig Horizontal/Vertical:   Two icons represented by an arrow showing
                              which direction you'll dig in. Once activated
                              the Beastie will dig a certain length. The
                              Beastie can be stopped at anytime by click the
                              mouse.
6: Crater Maker:              Does no character damage, but will create one
                              heck of a hole. Useful for obsticles.
7: Bridges:                   Will stick a bridge infront of you.
8: Rock Enhancer:             Out of your pocket comes a huge boulder.
                              This, like the bridges can be used for either
                              protection or climbing upon. Unlike bridges,
                              the boulder will Fall until it hits the
                              ground. This may be used as a stepping stone,
                              ie. You can build up a stack if you're high up
                                  which will save you dropping down too far
                                  and rendering y'self unconcious.

Tip: If the opposition is on the edge of a screen, why not use the shot gun
     to blow him/her right off!

     Same applies to if the opposition is on thin ground; blow the ground
     away from underneath 'em!

